JOHANNESBURG - NB Publishers says it believes the SA Revenue Service (Sars) has just conceded the truth of the parts of The President's Keepers in the application it has filed against the author, Jacques Pauw. Sars has reportedly filed papers in the Western Cape High Court against Pauw for "publishing confidential information" in his much-talked-about book about corruption in the government LISTEN: Security Agency lays charges against Jacques Pauw, spy agency employees In his affidavit, Sars commissioner Tom Moyane argues that Pauw revealed taxpayers' information, which is in contravention of the Tax Administration Act. Moyane wants Pauw to pay the costs should he oppose the application. eNCA